Real code is wider than a note bubble:

```
const rect = { x: node.x + node.width + LEAD, y: node.y - height / 2, w: NOTE_W, h: height };
if (bubbleOverlaps(rect, placed) && !sameSubtree(node, other)) {
    shiftSubtree(node, hit.y + hit.height + NOTE_GAP - rect.y);   // slide the whole group down
}
```

Every line above is longer than the bubble is wide. None of it may be lost:
the block wraps and keeps its indentation.

